I used 3D Home Architect ($90) years ago and it has very similar abilities to this $15 program. Before purchasing this though, I played with a few free download program from various vendors ranging in price from $60-$200. This program can do the basics even better than most expensive programs. I am very impressed with the simplicity in drawing walls, adding windows, doors, rooms, furniture, etc. Many of the other systems were complicated and took quite a learning curve just to draw walls. I would not expect to use program to turn plans directly over to a builder, but it will save you thousands in architectural fees by laying out your own floor-plan first. Once you design the interior, just turn it over to the architect for all the blueprint details. I'm using Windows 7 and it runs great. I was a little concerned by the description as to which OS versions it supports, but a 64-bit Win 7 runs great. I have not tried it on Windows 10, but will be soon.

I expect much better results from Webroot.

It was either incorrectly done or never fully installed. Also, the bios setting for the boot was set to automatic which had to remedied. The machine did a constant reboot. Could not get into Windows. Using a partition program I discovered that the partition which was supposed to be for Win10 was not set up properly...Had to repartition the HD. Finally did get a correct Win10 installed. It would be better to sell machines with a wiped HD and provide the Windows operating system on a DVD. I would give the product a higher rating, but due to the serious problems with the operating system setup conducted by the seller, I feel compelled to give it only 3 stars, and that might be stretching it..

I have been using an older version of Microsoft Word (the whole Microsoft Office suite) on my main laptop. I can't re-download it for some reason to my backup laptop (it won't let me even though I still have my registration code) that I keep at my parent's house so I decided to get one of the Open Source suites. I tried Apache first and it wasn't that good. Lots of issues with the word processing - the main program I use - so I uninstalled Apache and downloaded this suite - LibreOffice v4.3 for PC. AMAZING! Works just like Word in every way and you can open Libre documents in Word and vice versa. The suite is also compatible with Excel, PowerPoint and Publisher. I was surprised to learn that a lot of companies use and support Libre Open Office suite as their regular suite. Think about how cost effective this is for everyone. I guess I won't be buying Microsoft Office again. Ever. With the word processing program, I can create documents for reviews and then paste them right into the review form on Amazon with no problem. I can also transfer text into word documents easily. It's perfect. Publisher is also pretty amazing too. Highly recommend.

I'm a 65-year-old spinal cord injury survivor with a back and legs that are, well, 65 years old. It was literally a major pain to get on my knees to bathe my two dogs in the bathtub, which meant I would put off bathing them until they were absolutely filthy. This wash station changes everything. It fits perfectly within the bathtub and sits nice and stable. It's a comfortable size for my dogs and, best of all, is a great height for comfortable bathing. No more kneeling or crouching. I chose not to use the included restraints that attach to the bath; neither of my dogs were scared by the new bathtub. The only problem, and this is with me, not the tub, is that I had to resist leaning on the frame; I doubt that it would have held my weight. Note that I use a hand-held sprayer to give my dogs more of a shower than a bath. In other words, I do not fill the tub with water, so I don't know how it handles as a literal bath tub. But as a washing station, this table is excellent.

I had first heard about powdered Gatorade back when I had COVID and needed to work extra hard at staying hydrated, but it took me a while to give in and try it. I chose this variety pack because I know I like all three of these flavors in the bottle and I just couldn't beat the price. Plus I need something to help me keep my electrolytes up. What I love about the powders is I can easily put the packets into a ziploc bag and carry that around with me to add to my water bottle whenever I want to, no matter where I am. And again, it saves me a lot of money. For the most part, the flavors are still pretty good, but you do get a slight chalky, powdery taste at first. (Hence why I didn't give it a perfect 5*s.) But once all of the powder dissolves, you don't notice it as much and it still beats plain water. Another bonus is this is the G2, so you don't have all of the added sugars that you get in regular Gatorade. I am curious about other flavors, but again, these are my three favorites. I'm definitely reordering once I get low on this set.

For my purposes, this watch works just fine. However, I have only had the watch a couple months and the band already broke. I am lucky I didn't lose the whole watch as a necessary piece to hold the band together fell off. I really got the watch to keep time, track my sleep, and track my steps. The BP and heart rate readings are off by quite a bit, but I do believe that might be true of many watches like this. From what I read, consistency of the readings is the key. Sleep tracking is fair; it often continues to add hours of sleep when I am already out of bed. I would suggest making sure you look at your sleep totals as soon as you get up. I like knowing how many hours of deep/light sleep I have had, but again, there have been times I have been awake during the night for hours and the watch included those times in the total as well. The watch is easy to charge and I love the "find your phone" feature. For the price, this watch has served its purpose. I'd love to have a non-plastic band, but I don't believe any are available.

I have no idea why there are so many bad reviews on here! My son is 4 and we had so much fun doing all these experiments together. I followed them exactly for the plaster to set the volcano, no issues with it hardening first at all. My guess is some people didnÄôt mix things in the proper order? No idea. We made the mold, baked it in the oven on low and waited till the next day to paint it, painted it then waited till the next day for the eruptions.. the paint stayed on the whole time and now he has a fun painted volcano to keep playing with. I am surprised this is so well rated! The film starts with stories of hikers and hunters, who disappear and the explanation is never known, which makes an interesting story. Then, viewers are given a profile of people lost in the woods that is really a list you would expect to find when people in the wilderness get lost....weather events...close to sunset...near water, etc., that supposedly prove something sinister like aliens or monsters have abducted people. There is a recording of "mysterious" of language from something not human sounds was laughable. A high school band sees unexplained lights, (which is not that uncommon) that are hard to explain. At the same time, a female hunter sees a blob or orb. However, how this is related to missing hunters is never explained. We are given a blurred photo from a phone that mysteriously changed its settings on its own and this is purported evidence of paranormal phenomena. Just plain silly.

I genuinely feel embarrassed for some people. From missing persons cases (for which zero actual evidence was provided) to big foot creatures to....wait for it....the PREDATOR? Holy crap, what a load. Not worth the time.

Camping deep into the woods is full of scary noises, and that makes for good stories. Here we have, predictably, the insinuation of Predator, Big Foot, and Close Encounters. IMDB rewards this with a 7.1 rating! In my humble opinion, a more credible story line would have been the possibility of hunters hunting other hunters, as part of an initiation into a secret society, or a regular satanic practice.
Interesting, informative, and loved watching it. ItÄôs interesting what happened to these hunters when they were by themselves in the woods. I will watch it again.

I only took one or two of these before I wondered if they were potent enough to work. I looked at other reviews and then discovered that I should have noticed the labeled Country of Origin. While I'm fine buying consumer products that are made in China, some food products from China, including human and pet food, are known to have been contaminated and sometimes were even fatal. There is no way I want to be ingesting things from China unless I'm eating at a restaurant there and can judge for myself the general conditions of the business relative to my health and safety concerns. In this case, I choose not to take the risk and will find a different product in which to place my trust. By the way, I don't care that the ingredients were shipped in and packaged in the U.S., I'm not swallowing the package, and these were just too weak to work as expected for me, an average-size man. There was a reason the book was popular and the powers that be who decided to adapt it into a film sucked all the charm right out of the story. To begin with, the characterization was all wrong. The Lucy character is supposed to be quirky. She is a people pleaser who allows people to take advantage of her because she's lonely (she lost her good friend when the companies merged). Josh's "take no prisoners" attitude is an anathema to her, but the filmmakers got the characters all wrong. In the film, Lucy is spunky, but all of her quirks are missing. She usually seems on the verge of having a tantrum and is very pouty most of the time. I'm sure this is meant to be cute, but really it's just boring and more than a little annoying. As far as Josh goes, his character suffers more. I'm sure Stowell is a lovely person, but his portrayal of Josh was all wrong. He is supposed to be a character that scares the bee-jeebers out of everyone. Stowell, frankly, is rather bland in the role. He's a big Ken doll. There's not much of a personality there. There is nothing intriguing about him. He's supposed to be the backbone of the company while Lucy is the soul, and for some reason, the directors thought it would work for Hale and Crowell to be cardboard cutouts,removing all the quirks and idiosyncrasies that made the characters entertaining. The Hating Game is hardly Tolstoy, but it is a fun story and the film adaptation takes all the fun out, seeming to think the audience isn't going to notice. The character names and the most basic parts of the story line were the same, but that was about it. Too many of the details of the story that made it work we're taken out rendering it extremely bland and lifeless. If an adaptation is going to be made, they should take the (little bit of) extra time to do it right so the story works.

I thought I was going to find a terrible movie from what I heard from social media and reviews. I find it quite alarming that a community of people who are fighting so hard for individuality cannot accept this film as one individual's experience no matter how "right" or "wrong" anything might be. One reviewer spoke about the controversy of holding down severely autistic people during a meltdown or otherwise. This is controversial, meaning for some it helps and others it doesn't, hence the polarization of controversy. None of us in the peanut gallery can speak blanketed "shoulds" over the rest of the world this way. No one died and made anyone God. Where is the love? But also, film is artistic. And no one has a right to tell other people their artistic view of anything is right or wrong. Art IS subjective, that's why it is art. Even if we could say that holding down autistic people is wrong 100%, that doesn't mean this ARTIST has not witnessed this in their world as a truth that some autistics experience this whether it is right or wrong. The world is losing it's mind to this megalomania like they know everything right for everyone else because their trauma makes this righteous. That is ridiculous. Do more research and open your hearts more. None of us can puff ourselves up and call ourselves gods through these blaming and shaming, canceling everybody out and shutting everyone's voices down hate. That is the very reason these movements started (for individuality and voice) and everyone participating in this cancel culture is crapping on their own beliefs and values. Wake up! This movie is awesome. Watch yourself. Stop parroting everyone and be more accepting and loving. Everyone deserves love and respect, just like the movie advocates. Your pride doesn't give you a right to hate on other people and cancel them out. It's just hate.

It also prevented her from hurting herself. I think of it like a weighted blanket that is soothing. Everyone is different and that includes autistic individuals. What might work best for one person may not work at all for someone else. The technique of holding Music tightly worked for her. Sia did an amazing job. They let me know that often when you buy a product on Amazon they will replace the HP parts with what they are calling upgraded after-market parts. Those parts don't tend to last a long time and you end up with a useless computer. I strongly suggest that you research your products before you buy them or you too might end up with a very expensive piece of junk.

I love this laptop. Yes it's heavy, no it doesn't have a touch screen or backlit keyboard. The description gives the weight and there is no mention of a touch screen or backlit keyboard in the description, read the description and you will know what you are getting. I play games, surf the net, use word processing programs, watch DVD movies and everything else with this laptop. I love it, my games play smoothly and I have not had any issues. I always use my laptops close to a power source so when it starts to get low I can plug it in.

First of all Amazon review asked input on the three characteristics of this computer for which I am totally disappointed. Touch Screen, Battery Life, and Weight. There is no touch screen. For the price there should be. Battery life is a shameful 2 hours just doing word processing or web (no streaming, no major processor usage,etc.). And it heavy for a 2021 laptop. HP (or whoever made it) should try a little harder to get with the times. The processor, speed, RAM, etc. are good and must apparently be what you over pay $1000 for. The laptop itself is less than basic. The large platform with lots of excess real-estate makes it very difficult for a typists hands to find the keys. It is rather clunky. And it seems like the amount of pre-installed crappy programs that force you to sign up or give away your email address or blast advertisements at you is over the top. "S" mode is annoying it should be a simple 'opt in' option, rather than "fish around for an hour Google to figure out the pro/cons, and how to opt out". The DVD writer/player is pretty much a useless artifact and that technology should be replaced with touch screen AND a backlit keyboard. Seems cheap for being so expensive. My mistake for purchasing this brick for a grand.

While I am aware that I am now using Win10 S, and am also not yet slowed down thru several years of Windows Updates, as on my old laptop, this laptop is very fast. Startup takes less than a minute and surfing the web is much faster. PC's should have always run this quickly. Don't much like having to use Bing as my default browser, but I can always get Google, just can't make it my default browser. Shut down only takes about 5 seconds.

Except for a 2 hour battery life it is perfect. The instructions are incorrect as to removing the Windows 10 "S" mode. Simply type in "remove S mode" and it will be done automatically. The -1 star is related to battery life only
Very basic laptop, no back-lit keys which I thought all laptops come standard with. But does the job I need it to do.
I ordered this computer for personal use. It was easy to set up. I especially like the large screen.

First, I know reviews should be taken with a grain of salt but for those who complain about this device not using 5GHz, most IoT (plugs, bulbs, switches...etc) ONLY use 2.4GHz. Of many other reasons, it's because 2.4Ghz has a much longer range. It doesn't have as high of bandwidth capabilities but IoT devices obviously need very little bandwidth. Another downside to 2.4GHz is interference but longer range is more of a requirement than interference. I saw other complaints about not being able to schedule the plug via time of day. I don't know about the GE app but I'm not sure why you wouldn't use Google Home (might be others.) You can easily configure "Routines" and be much more detailed, if desired, than just time of day. This plug does support this through the Google Home app. The setup took me no longer than 2 minutes. I currently have it plugged into a space heater to test the max amperage abilities. I knocked off one star for two reasons. I couldn't find anywhere in the specs stating the max AMP capabilities. I bought this to control a pool pump which, while only rated at 10A, when it turns on and off it could spike higher than 10A and would fry any plug rated at 10A max. Since it's winter, I can't comment on this since space heaters do not have pumps which are what spikes the amperage. Lastly, the marketing is also a little misleading. I assumed I'd be able to control both plugs as if they were separate via wireless. That is not the case. Wirelessly you can turn the power on and off to both plugs but not individually. I guess how they are advertising it is you can physically turn each plug on and off because there is a button on the device. I was hoping to control each plug individually through routines and as desired from the Google Home app.

This product cannot be used to set an electronic device on a schedule. The app only allows the user to set a time to turn something on. The user cannot schedule a time to turn the same device off, nor set a recurring on/off schedule throughout the day. I bought this because the description stated I could use it to set a schedule. I wanted to set a humidifier to operate for an hour a few times a day. This was not possible.

Intro As a college student, having a reliable and portable workstation is extremely valuable. The New MacBook Air powered by the M1 chip is one of the most exciting devices recently released by Apple. Although it looks just like the previous models, the M1 chip delivers insanely great performance. Design and build Since its inception, Macbook AirÄôs design and build were one of its core selling points, and the Macbook Air M1 is no exception. It has that Signature Aluminium body that youÄôll see with the other Macbook Variants. The laptop not only looks premium but it definitely feels like your moneyÄôs worth. You can easily open this laptop with only one finger, this is possible because of the incredibly engineered hinge design done by apple. One of the things that the original Macbook air lacked for a while was a decent display, gone are the days of a 720p panel. And brought is a beautiful P3 Wide color gamut 2560*1440p panel, The overall viewing experience is awesome! The bezels are the same size as last year's model, which was kinda disappointing when compared to other laptops recently released, but it's not something that will ruin the overall viewing experience. The updated magic keyboard has better travel and also the gigantic mouse pad is always a blessing, IÄôm yet to find a trackpad on a laptop that I like better than the ones made by apple. The dual speaker grills on this laptop produce pretty decent sound, however, there is some slight distortion at high volumes. Storage Storage is also very important as a college student. As you're going to need some space to store all your documents, files, and Zoom Lectures. The MacBook Air comes with up to 2TB of SSD storage. This specific model I have only had 128GB of storage which honestly should be fine for most students, and if you donÄôt want to spend a lot of money you can always buy an external SSD or hard drive. This will cost you way less than what Apple offers. Portability As a College student in 2021, because of Covid, it's been kinda different, (Very small pause)all of our classes nowadays are held on zoom or some other online platform. So if you wanna use this laptop outside of a typical campus setting, then portability starts to matter. The MacBook Air weighs in at 2.75 pounds and is 15.6mm thick. This laptop will easily fit in most backups without feeling a noticeable weight difference. This is important to a lot of students, especially if you have back-to-back classes keeping in mind the average textbook weighs just over 4.6 pounds. This Laptop also easily fits in most handbags for women who were wondering. Reliability and Battery The Apple MacBook Air has proven itself as one of the most reliable laptops for a student this past decade. The Macbook Air is going to be a more compelling laptop for the students this, because of its insanely reliable performance for its price, but let's talk about the chip thatÄôs made all this possible. The biggest change this year is no doubt the M1 chip, the ARM-based chip is fast, like stupid fast. Applications open up real quick and the performance is consistently reliable. Not only can it easily fly through day-to-day tasks like browsing the internet and typing research papers, but it can also handle intensive tasks such as 4K video editing, in fact, I managed to edit an entire 4K video on the M1 MacBook air and the performance & exporting times were very impressive. Anyway, that was sometimes impossible on the previous-gens of Macbook air. Now if you are considering this device for video editing then I would highly recommend the 16 Gig variant. The next best thing aside from its insane performance is the incredible battery life, I think this is the best battery life I have ever seen on a laptop of this form factor. The laptop lasted me multiple days of light usage with the usual workload being typing, browsing, and streaming content. I can pull a full day of heavy usage with tasks like editing photos and videos. Conclusion Overall thereÄôs a quote that says, ÄúSpeed is irrelevant if you are going in the wrong directionÄù. (Mahatma Gandhi). The Macbook Air M1 has set a new benchmark for consistent performance and delivers insanely awesome battery life which makes the overall experience pretty fire. Its Portability, reliability, and speed not only make this a great investment for a student but also for anybody whoÄôs always on the go, and IÄôm personally really excited for the direction that Apple is heading towards with their new M lineup of processers.
